{
  "text": "In the case of a lipid membrane in water, the only dimensional parameters that can span various orders of magnitudes are σ 0 and z 0 . For σ 0 ≥ 10 −8 N/m, i.e., for realistic membrane tensions [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , and for z 0 ≥ 5 µm, we will see in the following that the only relevant dimensionless parameters in the dynamics of the membrane are µ and",
  "correct_citation": {
